article.headline: Stetson 75, Campbell 72
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon and Anthony Register combined for 43 points to lead Stetson to a 75-72 victory over Campbell on Thursday night. Gordon led with 22 points and had six assists, while Register had 21 points and eight rebounds as the Hatters (9-11, 7-7 Atlantic Sun) won for the seventh time in its last 10 games. Dominique Klein led Campbell with 18 points and 10 rebounds while Corey Parker added 13 points as the Fighting Camels (2-19, 2-12) lost their 28th straight road game going back to January of 2002. Stetson led by 65-49 with 4:22 left to play before Campbell made a late run, twice cutting the Hatters' lead to four points in the last minute. However, Register converted five of six free throws in the last 53 seconds to protect Stetson's lead.
